<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph lastPageNumber="12" pageNumber="11">
Diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachycephalum">Pachycara brachycephalum</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from its congeners by the following combination of characters: pelvic fins present or (rarely) absent; branchiostegal rays 6; no occipital pores; lateral line with ventral and mediolateral branches, ventral originating behind posteriormost postorbital pore, mediolateral originating on vertical through pectoral fin margin or somewhat anterior to margin when fin appressed; gill rakers blunt and triangular except in specimens over about 320 mm SL; vertebrae 20-27 + 71-86 = 92-113.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="12">
Remarks. This species was thoroughly redescribed on the basis of 76 specimens, including four syntypes, by Anderson (1988). All of these possessed the typical, rudimentary pelvic fins of most zoarcids. The new Weddell and Ross seas material adds no further data except the following: Pelvic fins are absent in RUSI 54819, MNHN 1990-635, one (105 mm SL) in ISH 16/91, 28 in RUSI 54825 and one (217 mm SL) in RUSI 54821. The other in ISH 16/91, ISH 9/91, MNHN 1990-633, 1990-634, two (205, 214 mm SL) in RUSI 54821 and four (202-228 mm SL) in RUSI 54825 have regressed, nipple-like pelvic fins as described for 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:05AB8F03-EC44-49D5-89B9-79238CF1A3E0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara rimae Anderson 1989:235" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rimae">P. rimae</taxonomicName>
by Anderson (1989). Five zoarcid species are now known in which pelvic fins are present or absent (others are 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EB4BEA68-DB42-4604-9638-2DC5CBB7849C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara mesoporum Anderson 1989:237" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mesoporum">Pachycara mesoporum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B9B84B15-511B-49D7-8F09-59C7443278A4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara sulaki Anderson 1989:231" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sulaki">P. sulaki</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7538F967-02E6-4FC0-92A6-C76F6ACF1ADF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Lycenchelys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Lycenchelys monstrosa Anderson 1982:208" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="monstrosa">Lycenchelys monstrosa</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Crossostomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chilensis">Crossostomus chilensis</taxonomicName>
(Anderson, 1994: 13).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1CC7472-B781-4622-8C6A-22B2989E3DBB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara goni Anderson 1991:155" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goni">Pachycara goni</taxonomicName>
from the Weddell Sea was diagnosed in part on its furcate gill rakers, like those of the West African 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B3D8A4C7-9A2D-4685-B753-B81CE8DCD188" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara crossacanthum Anderson 1989:230" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crossacanthum">P. crossacanthum</taxonomicName>
(Anderson, 1989, 1991). Three specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachycephalum">P. brachycephalum</taxonomicName>
in SAM 34531, 322-356 mm SL, the largest known, had furcate gill rakers as well, thus this state seems to have an ontogenetic component in 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachycephalum">P. brachycephalum</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1CC7472-B781-4622-8C6A-22B2989E3DBB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara goni Anderson 1991:155" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goni">P. goni</taxonomicName>
(single known specimen at 262 mm SL) is distinguised from 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachycephalum">P. brachycephalum</taxonomicName>
by its higher vertebral and unpaired fin-ray counts (vert. 27 + 98; D 118; A 99), seven suborbital pores and more posterior origin of the mediolateral lateral line. Specimens USNM 356658 of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachycephalum">P. brachycephalum</taxonomicName>
had the dorsal-fin origin associated with vertebrae 8-9, extending this character from vertebrae 3-7 (Anderson, 1988) to vertebrae 3-9. These also extend the lower depth range from 1810 m (Anderson, 1988) to 2542 m, overlapping that of the presumed lower-slope 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1CC7472-B781-4622-8C6A-22B2989E3DBB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara goni Anderson 1991:155" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goni">Pachycara goni</taxonomicName>
(Anderson, 1991), caught at 2025-2037 m.
</paragraph>
